        <type>double</type>
        <definition>double faiss::detail::chi2_quantile_wh</definition>
        <argsstring>(int p, double alpha)</argsstring>
        <name>chi2_quantile_wh</name>
        <qualifiedname>faiss::detail::chi2_quantile_wh</qualifiedname>
        <param>
          <type>int</type>
          <declname>p</declname>
        </param>
        <param>
          <type>double</type>
          <declname>alpha</declname>
        </param>
        <briefdescription>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>Chi-squared quantile via cube-root approximation. Validated to within 2% of scipy for <computeroutput>p in [16, d]</computeroutput> and <computeroutput>alpha &lt;= 1 - 1e-6</computeroutput>. Accuracy degrades for smaller <computeroutput>p</computeroutput> or for <computeroutput>alpha</computeroutput> near 1. </para>
        </detaileddescription>
