      <memberdef kind="function" id="namespacefaiss_1_1detail_1ac3611a8d1b22c809d8805a48efddff1a" prot="public" static="no" const="no" explicit="no" inline="no" virt="non-virtual">
        <type>std::vector&lt; float &gt;</type>
        <definition>std::vector&lt; float &gt; faiss::detail::precompute_ad_thresholds</definition>
        <argsstring>(int d, double epsilon)</argsstring>
        <name>precompute_ad_thresholds</name>
        <qualifiedname>faiss::detail::precompute_ad_thresholds</qualifiedname>
        <param>
          <type>int</type>
          <declname>d</declname>
        </param>
        <param>
          <type>double</type>
          <declname>epsilon</declname>
        </param>
        <briefdescription>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>Build ADSampling threshold table of size <computeroutput>d + 1</computeroutput>: coeff[p] = chi2_quantile_wh(p, 1 - epsilon) / d.</para>
<para>Indexing: coeff[0] is reserved (left at 0.0f). coeff[1..15] are computed but NOT accuracy-bounded — callers requiring the 2% scipy tolerance must consume only coeff[16..d]. <ref refid="structfaiss_1_1SuperKMeans" kindref="compound">SuperKMeans</ref> enforces this via its <computeroutput>d_prime_min = 16</computeroutput> parameter. </para>
        </detaileddescription>
